attributes.name: aria-activedescendant
attributes.comment: Identifies the currently active element when DOM focus is on a composite widget, textbox, group, or application.

attributes.name: aria-atomic
attributes.comment: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.

attributes.name: aria-autocomplete
attributes.comment: Indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for an input and specifies how predictions would be presented if they are made.

attributes.name: aria-busy
attributes.comment: Indicates an element is being modified and that assistive technologies MAY want to wait until the modifications are complete before exposing them to the user.

attributes.name: aria-checked
attributes.comment: Indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets.

attributes.name: aria-colcount
attributes.comment: Defines the total number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-colindex
attributes.comment: Defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-colspan
attributes.comment: Defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-controls
attributes.comment: Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element.

attributes.name: aria-current
attributes.comment: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.
attributes.value: boolean | false | true | page | step | location | date | time

attributes.name: aria-describedby
attributes.comment: Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object.

attributes.name: aria-details
attributes.comment: Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object.

attributes.name: aria-disabled
attributes.comment: Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.

attributes.name: aria-dropeffect
attributes.comment: Indicates what functions can be performed when a dragged object is released on the drop target.
attributes.value: none | copy | execute | link | move | popup

attributes.name: aria-errormessage
attributes.comment: Identifies the element that provides an error message for the object.

attributes.name: aria-expanded
attributes.comment: Indicates whether the element, or another grouping element it controls, is currently expanded or collapsed.

attributes.name: aria-flowto
attributes.comment:
Identifies the next element (or elements) in an alternate reading order of content which, at the user's discretion,
allows assistive technology to override the general default of reading in document source order.

attributes.name: aria-grabbed
attributes.comment: Indicates an element's "grabbed" state in a drag-and-drop operation.

attributes.name: aria-haspopup
attributes.comment: Indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.
attributes.value: boolean | false | true | menu | listbox | tree | grid | dialog

attributes.name: aria-hidden
attributes.comment: Indicates whether the element is exposed to an accessibility API.

attributes.name: aria-invalid
attributes.comment: Indicates the entered value does not conform to the format expected by the application.

attributes.name: aria-keyshortcuts
attributes.comment: Indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.

attributes.name: aria-label
attributes.comment: Defines a string value that labels the current element.

attributes.name: aria-labelledby
attributes.comment: Identifies the element (or elements) that labels the current element.

attributes.name: aria-level
attributes.comment: Defines the hierarchical level of an element within a structure.

attributes.name: aria-live
attributes.comment: Indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.

attributes.name: aria-modal
attributes.comment: Indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.

attributes.name: aria-multiline
attributes.comment: Indicates whether a text box accepts multiple lines of input or only a single line.

attributes.name: aria-multiselectable
attributes.comment: Indicates that the user may select more than one item from the current selectable descendants.

attributes.name: aria-orientation
attributes.comment: Indicates whether the element's orientation is horizontal, vertical, or unknown/ambiguous.

attributes.name: aria-owns
attributes.comment: Identifies an element (or elements) in order to define a visual, functional, or contextual parent/child relationship between DOM elements where the DOM hierarchy cannot be used to represent the relationship.

attributes.name: aria-placeholder
attributes.comment:
Defines a short hint (a word or short phrase) intended to aid the user with data entry when the control has no value.
A hint could be a sample value or a brief description of the expected format.

attributes.name: aria-posinset
attributes.comment: Defines an element's number or position in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.

attributes.name: aria-pressed
attributes.comment: Indicates the current "pressed" state of toggle buttons.

attributes.name: aria-readonly
attributes.comment: Indicates that the element is not editable, but is otherwise operable.

attributes.name: aria-relevant
attributes.comment: Indicates what notifications the user agent will trigger when the accessibility tree within a live region is modified.
attributes.value: additions | additions text | all | removals | text

attributes.name: aria-required
attributes.comment: Indicates that user input is required on the element before a form may be submitted.

attributes.name: aria-roledescription
attributes.comment: Defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.

attributes.name: aria-rowcount
attributes.comment: Defines the total number of rows in a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-rowindex
attributes.comment: Defines an element's row index or position with respect to the total number of rows within a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-rowspan
attributes.comment: Defines the number of rows spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.

attributes.name: aria-selected
attributes.comment: Indicates the current "selected" state of various widgets.

attributes.name: aria-setsize
attributes.comment: Defines the number of items in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.

attributes.name: aria-sort
attributes.comment: Indicates if items in a table or grid are sorted in ascending or descending order.

attributes.name: aria-valuemax
attributes.comment: Defines the maximum allowed value for a range widget.

attributes.name: aria-valuemin
attributes.comment: Defines the minimum allowed value for a range widget.

attributes.name: aria-valuenow
attributes.comment: Defines the current value for a range widget.

attributes.name: aria-valuetext
attributes.comment: Defines the human readable text alternative of aria-valuenow for a range widget.
